message.content:
A 'Turdus migratorius' is a species of migratory songbird commonly known as the American robin.
It has a distinctive orange-red breast and a greyish-brown back.
Its wings are dark with white markings.
The feathers have a smooth texture and the beak is sharply pointed.
They are approximately 10 inches in length and weigh between 70-85 grams.
Turdus migratorius are commonly found in North America.
They are often seen in suburban areas hunting for earthworms and insects on lawns and gardens.
